RM  24710389
RT  Lactate racemase is a nickel-dependent enzyme activated by a
RT  widespread maturation system.
RA  Desguin B, Goffin P, Viaene E, Kleerebezem M, Martin-Diaconescu V,
RA  Maroney MJ, Declercq JP, Soumillion P, Hols P;
RL  Nat Commun. 2014;5:3615.
RN  [2]
RM  27114550
RT  Nickel-pincer cofactor biosynthesis involves LarB-catalyzed
RT  pyridinium carboxylation and LarE-dependent sacrificial sulfur
RT  insertion.
RA  Desguin B, Soumillion P, Hols P, Hausinger RP;
RL  Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A. 2016;113:5598-5603. 
CC  LarB, LarE and LarC are involved in the synthesis of the nickel-pincer
CC  cofactor of lactate racemase LarA. LarB converts nicotinic acid adenine
CC  dinucleotide (NaAD) into pyridinium-3,5-biscarboxylic acid mononucleotide
CC  (P2CMN). LarE incorporates two sulfur atoms to yield P2TMN, and LarC donates
CC  Ni, so that the mature cofactor becomes covalently attached to LarA [2]. 
**  In species where larA is absent, this pathway could be used to generate a
**  pincer complex in other enzymes.
